  "prompt": "Can we use Jio 4G sim to 3G handsets?",
  "response": "No, you **cannot use a Jio 4G SIM in a 3G handset**. Reliance Jio operates exclusively on **4G LTE (VoLTE)** technology, meaning its network is designed to work only on 4G-enabled devices that support VoLTE (Voice over LTE). \n\nHere are the key reasons why it won't work:\n\n1. **Jio's Network is 4G-only**: Jio does not have 2G or 3G networks. If your handset does not support 4G LTE and VoLTE, it cannot connect to Jio's network.\n\n2. **VoLTE Requirement**: Jio uses VoLTE for voice calls, so even if your device supports 4G data, it must also support VoLTE to make calls. The majority of 3G handsets lack this capability.\n\n3. **SIM Activation**: During the initial setup, Jio SIMs need to connect to a 4G VoLTE network for activation, which a 3G handset cannot do.\n\n### Solution\nIf you want to use Jio services, you will need a device that supports **4G LTE and VoLTE**. You can check your device's specifications or contact the manufacturer to confirm its compatibility. If your current handset is not compatible, you may need to upgrade to a 4G-enabled device.",
